==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trachystomata
<hw>Tra`chy*stom"a*ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/ rough + <ets>stoma</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An order of tailed aquatic amphibians, including
<gen>Siren</gen> and <gen>Pseudobranchus</gen>. They have anterior legs
only, are eel-like in form, and have no teeth except a small patch on
the palate. The external gills are persistent through life.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Trachyte</ent>⟦br⟧
